                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that the Russian Government formally agrees to the submission
                    of the circumstances of the North Sea incident to a special tribunal as provided
                    by articles 9 and 14 of The Hague convention; that the preliminary inquiry is to
                    be conducted at Vigo, where the fleet is to remain at present.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
